<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <!-- for tailwind (uncomment when ready to use) -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">

    <title>Select A Playlist Length</title>
</head>

<body>
<div class="main">
    <div class="flex justify-center">
        <p id="access" class="hidden"> <%= access_token ;%></p>

        <div class="navbar">
            <a href="/home">
                <img src="Logo.svg" class="p-2 h-14" />
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p>Currently uses a hardcoded array of dummy song lengths, displays the options for a fifteen minute playlist over
        (left) and under (right).</p>
    <a id="playlistOver" class="hover:text-xl pr-6 font-montserrat font-bold text-main-green text-lg" href="/player">15:30</a>

    <a id="playlistUnder" class="hover:text-xl pr-6 font-montserrat font-bold text-main-green text-lg" href="/player">15:00</a>

</div>

<script src="/playlists.js"></script>
</body>

</html>
